                            <comment id="14465512" author="blackdrag" created="Sat, 1 Nov 2008 17:16:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;that is strange... I thought we already have a check for the usage of &quot;this&quot; in a case like above... yes, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-500&quot; title=&quot;Can&amp;#39;t pass this in super()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-500&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-500&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; sounds very much like that bug... hmm. let me look at Verifier... in fact line 392 is expected to report this as an compilation error. .. but when I look at this code now, I have the feeling this nether really worked right, because the code looks as if it has some obvious bugs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14466854" author="roshandawrani" created="Sat, 25 Apr 2009 09:53:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In Constructor body, if &quot;this&quot; or &quot;super&quot; was found referred in arguments list of a ConstructorCallExpression, a compiler error is thrown as in the case of MethodCallExpression.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
